# Paperwork Labs Brand Guide

## Brand Architecture

```
PAPERWORK LABS (Holding Company - paperworklabs.com)
  "We build tools that eliminate paperwork."
  │
  ├── CONSUMER BRANDS (free, own domains, own CTA hue, trinity-palette mark)
  │   ├── FileFree ........... filefree.ai (free tax filing)
  │   ├── LaunchFree ......... launchfree.ai (free LLC formation)
  │   ├── AxiomFolio ......... axiomfolio.com (portfolio + signals; absorbed 2026 Q2)
  │   └── Trinkets ........... tools.filefree.ai (utility tools)
  │
  ├── CONSUMER META-PRODUCT (B2C; primary standalone product)
  │   └── Brain .............. (external name + domain TBD pending availability)
  │       Life-intelligence engine; subsumes other products as "skills"
  │       See docs/BRAIN_ARCHITECTURE.md (D49, F90, G01)
  │
  ├── B2B BRAND (paid, one platform)
  │   └── Distill ............ distill.tax (compliance automation APIs + CPA SaaS)
  │       ├── Distill for CPAs (SaaS, $49-199/mo)
  │       ├── Distill Tax API (per-return)
  │       ├── Distill Formation API (per-filing)
  │       └── Distill Compliance API (per-action)
  │
  └── PUBLISHING (incidental; LLC umbrella only, no visible branding)
      Children's books in Hindi and other languages, AI-illustrated
      Imprint attribution: copyright page only ("Published by Paperwork Labs LLC")
      Books carry their own series brand on covers + spines
```

**Why this architecture**: Consumer brands are free and distinct - each owns a clear paperwork category. Brain is the meta-product whose "skills" are the consumer brands. Distill unifies all B2B under one brand (Stripe model, not Intuit model). Paperwork Labs is both the infrastructure company and the LLC umbrella for incidental ventures (publishing).

## Brand Names

- **Company name**: Paperwork Labs (two words, both capitalized)
- **Legal entity**: Paperwork Labs LLC
- **Domain**: paperworklabs.com
